PEOPLE, Respondent, v. GIRARD, Appellant. (Supreme Court, General Term, Fourth Department. February 15, 1894.) ■ Action by- the people against Anthony Girard.

Argued before HARDIN, P. J., and MARTIN and MERWIN,- JJ.

No opinion. Leave granted to appeal to the court of appeals, as the case involves a question' of law that ought to be reviewed by- that court.. See 26 N. Y. Supp. 272.
